All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
BackGround
Background object extended from Sprite that will display image of the selected background from assets folder
Character
Character objects represents main character class in our game.
Collidable
Collidable class that will enable colliding with another Collidable objects, and it extends from Sprite class
Enemy
Enemy class used to represent obstacles/monsters.
GamePanel
GamePanel is used to display whole panel of the game and log messages.
Helper
Helper interface defines all the constants is used in our game.
JumpBehavior
JumpBehavior is an interface, and it is simple example of Strategy Design Pattern.
JumpPowerUp
D Type PowerUp Extends from PowerUp object, but it doesn't have any multiplier.
LongJump
LongJump simply does make main character jump longer.
Main
Main class to start our game.
PowerUp
PowerUp abstract class do certain power ups to the main character.
PowerUpDecorator
PowerUpDecorator class extended from PowerUp object.
ShortJump
ShortJump simply does make main character jump Shorter.
Sprite
Abstract class used for keeping track of images ,setting their locations and drawing images
x10Multiplier
C-Type Power Up x10Multiplier decorator class extends PowerUpDecorator.
x1Multiplier
Concrete PowerUp class.
x2Multiplier
A-Type Power Up x2Multiplier decorator class extends PowerUpDecorator.
x5Multiplier
B-Type Power Up x5Multiplier decorator class extends PowerUpDecorator.
